  "title": "A Baby Star and a Big Competition",
  "article_text": "A huge star in the sky can sing, but I doubt it because stars do not make sounds. I refer to a famous theory that stars are like babies in space. For instance, one cold quarter of the sky has a new star that is growing. My friend proposed an argument that this baby star is more successful than others. We assume the star's style is very special because it can push away dust. The competition between stars is interesting, but this one is the biggest. An adult star is bigger, but the baby star is more active. I sent a message to my teacher about this star, and she gave me a reference book. I must clean my room, but I want to advance my study of stars. I fill my notebook with facts, and I tend to look at the sky every night.",
